dataIdInfo.idPurp: The BCPL parcels layer references land parcels owned and managed by the agency to generate revenue for the various trust funds it administers. The layer aids BCPL staff in defining land managment and real estate activities and facilitates the meeting of the agency's mission and goals. It is appropriate to use this data for general information purposes only.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: The Wisconsin Board of Commissioners of Public Lands (BCPL), as the oldest state agency, has been managing forest lands since the States inception. As part of that management it has built and maintained a database of it's current holdings, approximately 75,000 acres, throughout the State. This dataset uses a scale factor of .999600, with a resolution of 1 meter. It uses a WTM83/91 projected coordinate system.

Consts.useLimit: Since ongoing surveys continually add new information, shapes older than one year are considered outdated. Products created using this layer should always include the date it was generated. (Refer to publication information section of this document.) This dataset is intended as a reference only, and is not intended to be used to define legal boundries.
